sentence:
He started 
making noises such as Frank had never heard before; 
he was hissing and spitting without drawing breath.

By Gryffindor, the bravest were 
Prized far beyond the rest; 

For Ravenclaw, the cleverest 
Would always be the best; 

For Hufflepuff, hard workers were 
Most worthy of admission; 

And power-hungry Slytherin 
Loved those of great ambition.

... Cho was a year older than he was; 
she was very pretty; she was a very good Quidditch 
player, and she was also very popular.

Half a dozen mermen were pulling him away 
from Hermione, shaking their green-haired heads, 
and laughing.

Harry looked around; 
Dumbledore was sitting beside him again, wearing 
different robes.

And then 
Wormtail lowered the creature into the cauldron; 
there was a hiss, and it vanished below the surface; 
Harry heard its frail body hit the bottom with a soft 
thud.

It was even a relief; 




he felt almost as though something poisonous were 
being extracted from him.

Even though I vos 
from Durmstrang — with Karkaroff,” he added, 
scowling.

The rest of the journey passed pleasantly enough; 
Harry wished it could have gone on all summer, in 
fact, and that he would never arrive at King’s Cross .
